  "local_port": 55544,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Who are the best employment lawyers in the SF Bay Area?",
  "response": "The San Francisco Bay Area is home to many highly skilled employment lawyers who specialize in various aspects of labor and employment law. While \"best\" is subjective and depends on your specific needs, here are some well-regarded employment law firms and individuals in the SF Bay Area:\n\n### Top Employment Law Firms in the SF Bay Area:\n1. **Littler Mendelson P.C.** (San Francisco)  \n   - One of the largest and most recognized employment law firms in the U.S., focusing on employer-side representation.\n   \n2. **Outten & Golden LLP** (San Francisco)  \n   - Known for representing employees in cases involving discrimination, harassment, wrongful termination, and wage issues.\n\n3. **Rudolph, Beer, & Gill LLP** (San Jose)  \n   - Specializes in employment law for both employees and employers, focusing on litigation, advice, and counseling.\n\n4. **Bryan Schwartz Law** (Oakland)  \n   - A boutique firm representing employees in discrimination, whistleblower, wage and hour, and class action cases.\n\n5. **Fisher Phillips LLP** (San Francisco)  \n   - A national firm with a strong focus on employer-side employment law, including litigation, compliance, and training.\n\n6. **Lawless & Lawless** (San Francisco)  \n   - A boutique firm representing employees in cases involving discrimination, harassment, wrongful termination, and wage disputes.\n\n### Notable Employment Lawyers in the SF Bay Area:\n1. **Mark A. McDonald** (Outten & Golden LLP)  \n   - Specializes in employee-side litigation, particularly in whistleblower and discrimination cases.\n\n2. **Bryan Schwartz** (Bryan Schwartz Law)  \n   - A prominent advocate for employees in class actions and individual cases involving wage and hour disputes.\n\n3. **David M. Rosenberg** (Rudolph, Beer, & Gill LLP)  \n   - Known for handling complex employment litigation and counseling for both employees and employers.\n\n4. **Lori E. Andrus** (Andrus Anderson LLP)  \n   - Focuses on gender discrimination, equal pay, and class action cases on behalf of employees.\n\n5. **Alison B. Wetherfield** (Lawless & Lawless)  \n   - Specializes in employee-side cases involving discrimination, harassment, and wrongful termination.\n\n### How to Choose the Best Employment Lawyer for You:\n- **Identify Your Needs:** Determine whether you need representation for employee-side issues (e.g., discrimination, wrongful termination) or employer-side matters (e.g., compliance, litigation defense).\n- **Research Experience:** Look for lawyers with specific experience in your type of case.\n- **Read Reviews:** Check client testimonials and peer reviews on platforms like Avvo, Martindale-Hubbell, or Google.\n- **Schedule Consultations:** Many lawyers offer free consultations to discuss your case and determine if they\u2019re a good fit.\n\nIf you have a specific issue or need more tailored recommendations, feel free to provide additional details!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
